<item>
            <title>[LU-1693] filter_do_bio() and osd_do_bio() should set bi_rw before calling bio_add_page()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1693</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;filter_do_bio() calls bio_add_page() without setting the direction of the bio.  In bio_add_page() the direction is passed on to the merge_bvec_fn() if defined.  raid5_mergeable_bvec() does check the direction and setting it correctly improves write bandwidth by allowing for full stripe writes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I assume that this is equally true of osd_do_bio().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
